Alpha Diversity

#Prep data
mic.assmblg <- data_rarefied
results <- estimate_richness(mic.assmblg, measures = c('Shannon', 'Simpson', 'Observed'))
d <- sample_data(mic.assmblg)
dunnTest(results$Observed~ factor(d$Sampling_time), method = "bon")

Dunn (1964) Kruskal-Wallis multiple comparison
  p-values adjusted with the Bonferroni method.

#Pheno <- Pheno + scale_colour_manual(values = c("#CD6821","#CD6821","#CD6821","#CD6821","#158172","#158172","#158172","#158172","#214788","#214788","#214788","#214788"))

#shapiro.test(aov(results$Shannon~d$time_point)$residuals)
t1_shannon<-kruskal.test(results$Shannon~ factor(d$Developmental_stage))
dunnTest(results$Shannon~ factor(d$Developmental_stage), method = "bon")

#shapiro.test(aov(results$Simpson~d$time_point)$residuals)
t1_simpson<-kruskal.test(results$Simpson~ factor(d$status))
dunnTest(results$Simpson~ factor(d$status), method = "bon")

#shapiro.test(aov(results$Observed~d$time_point)$residuals)
#Meets normality assumption but we will use kruskall wallis for congruency
t1_observed<-kruskal.test(results$Observed~ factor(d$status))
dunnTest(results$Observed~ factor(d$status), method = "bon")

Indicator species analysis

Generate human readable taxonomic labels.

# generate a vector containing the full taxonomy path for all OTUs
wholetax <- do.call(paste, c(as.data.frame(tax_table(data_transformed))
                  [c("Kingdom", "Phylum", "Class", "Order", "Family", "Genus")], 
                  sep = "__"))  # to distinguish from "_" within tax ranks

# turn the otu_table into a data.frame
otu_export <- as.data.frame(otu_table(data_transformed))
tmp <- names(otu_export)
tmp2<-seq(1:nrow(data.frame(tmp)))

# paste wholetax and OTU_ids together
for(i in 1:length(tmp)){
names(tmp)[i] = paste(wholetax[i], tmp2[i], sep = "__")
}

# overwrite old names
names(otu_export) <- names(tmp)

AT=1 means the taxa only occurs in that group and in no others. BT= 1 means all samples in that group have that taxa.

Indicator species analysis for time point.

indval_t <- multipatt(otu_export, samp_data$time_point, control = how(nperm = 1000), func = "indval")
summary(indval_t, alpha = 0.01, At = 0.5, Bt = 0.5, indvalcomp = T)
summary(indval_t, alpha = 0.01, At = 0.7, Bt = 0.8 , indvalcomp = T)

#max.order constrains the associations to a single group where as above it can be associated with multiple groups
indval_1_t <- multipatt(otu_export, samp_data$time_point, control = how(nperm = 1000), max.order = 1, func = "indval")
summary(indval_1_t, alpha = 0.01, At = 0.5, Bt = 0.8, indvalcomp = T)
summary(indval_1_t, alpha = 0.01, At = 0.7, Bt = 0.8 , indvalcomp = T)

indval_2_t <- multipatt(otu_export, samp_data$time_point, control = how(nperm = 1000), max.order = 2, func = "indval")
summary(indval_2_t, alpha = 0.01, At = 0.5, Bt = 0.5, indvalcomp = T)
summary(indval_2_t, alpha = 0.01, At = 0.7, Bt = 0.8 , indvalcomp = T)

sigtab<-sigtabT1T3
# Phylum order
x = tapply(sigtab$log2FoldChange, sigtab$Phylum, function(x) max(x))
x = sort(x, TRUE)
sigtab$Phylum = factor(as.character(sigtab$Phylum), levels=names(x))
# Genus order
x = tapply(sigtab$log2FoldChange, sigtab$Genus, function(x) max(x))
x = sort(x, TRUE)
sigtab$Genus = factor(as.character(sigtab$Genus), levels=names(x))

data_rarefied_genus <- tax_glom(data_rarefied, "Genus")

res2 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("Sampling_time", "T1", "T3"))

#make box n whisker plot of phylum for summarized time point data
silk_workingr <- transform_sample_counts(time_merged, function(x) x/sum(x))
# agglomerate taxa
glom <- tax_glom(silk_workingr, taxrank = 'Phylum')
#create dataframe
dat <- psmelt(glom)
#make phylum a character
dat$Phylum <- as.character(dat$Phylum)
library(plyr)
medians <- ddply(dat, ~Phylum, function(x) c(median=median(x$Abundance)))
remainder <- medians[medians$median <= 0.0001,]$Phylum
dat[dat$Phylum %in% remainder,]$Phylum <- 'Remainder'
ggplot(dat,
       aes(x=Phylum,
           y=Abundance)) + geom_boxplot() + coord_flip()

Indicator analysis for genotype

data_rarefied_genus <- tax_glom(data_rarefied, "Genus")

diagdds <- phyloseq_to_deseq2(data_rarefied_genus, ~ genotype)
diagdds <- DESeq(diagdds, test="Wald", fitType="parametric")

#no indicator taxa at the family level.

res1 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("genotype", "SALK_072930C", "CS3797")) # none
res2 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("genotype", "SALK_072930C", "CS6230")) # 1
res3 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("genotype", "SALK_072930C", "CS9869")) # 2
res4 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("genotype", "SALK_072930C", "CS6673")) # none

res5 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("genotype", "CS3797", "CS6230")) # 1
res6 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("genotype", "CS3797", "CS9869")) #2
res7 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("genotype", "CS3797", "CS6673")) # none

res8 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("genotype", "CS6230", "CS9869")) # none
res9 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("genotype", "CS6230", "CS6673")) # none

res10 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("genotype", "CS9869", "CS6673")) # none
  
res<-res6
alpha = 0.01
sigtab <- res[which(res$padj < alpha), ]
sigtab <- cbind(as(sigtab, "data.frame"), as(tax_table(data_rarefied)[rownames(sigtab), ], "matrix"))
head(sigtab)

Indicator analysis for flowering status

data_rarefied_genus <- tax_glom(data_rarefied, "Genus")

diagdds <- phyloseq_to_deseq2(data_rarefied_genus, ~ Developmental_stage)
diagdds <- DESeq(diagdds, test="Wald", fitType="parametric")

res1 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("Developmental_stage", "senesce", "flowering")) # 1
res2 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("Developmental_stage", "senesce", "fruiting")) # 2
res3 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("Developmental_stage", "senesce", "vegetative")) # 3

res4 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("Developmental_stage", "flowering", "fruiting")) # 4

res5 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("Developmental_stage", "flowering", "vegetative")) # 5

res6 <- DESeq2::results(diagdds,  contrast = c("Developmental_stage", "fruiting", "vegetative")) # 6

res<-res4
  
alpha = 0.01
sigtab <- res[which(res$padj < alpha), ]
sigtab <- cbind(as(sigtab, "data.frame"), as(tax_table(data_rarefied)[rownames(sigtab), ], "matrix"))
View(sigtab)
